# Sentinel — Cursor Project Rules

`AGENTS.md` is the **canonical operating guide**, `PLAN.md` is the **full plan**, and
`ROADMAP.md` is the **PR-sized execution breakdown** (per-phase tasks with What /
Goal / How-to-test). Read all three. This rule restates the non-negotiables and
always applies.

## Project (one line)
**Sentinel** — an **AI risk-guardian real-yield account** on **Mantle** (chain ID
5000). Users deposit **USDC**; an AI agent (Z.AI) earns tokenized-Treasury
(**USDY**) yield with an **Aave v3** USDC liquidity floor, and **autonomously
de-risks on-chain** into **AUSD**/USDC on RWA danger (depeg, oracle staleness,
issuer/regulatory shock), recording every decision **and its evidence** on-chain
under an **ERC-8004** identity. Track: **AI × RWA (Application path)**. The
verifiable autonomous defense — not the swap-to-USDY — is the product.

## Non-negotiables
- **1delta = data + optional swap routing ONLY.** Never in the custody/execution
  path. The vault must never execute arbitrary third-party calldata. Execution
  happens only via our own adapters (`UsdyAdapter`, `AaveV3Adapter`, `AusdAdapter`)
  that call protocols/DEXs directly with on-chain `minOut`/guardrail checks.
- **Guardrails are final.** LLM proposes → deterministic validator checks against
  guardrails → immutable on-chain guardrails are the backstop. The model is never
  the last line of defense. Guardrails: max weight/bucket, min idle+Aave liquidity
  buffer, max slippage, token/venue whitelist, rebalance-frequency cap, per-tx caps,
  pause/kill switch, add-strategy timelock, depeg/oracle-deviation guard.
- **AI only where it beats an algorithm.** Keep yield/optimization/peg/oracle/
  liquidity/execution deterministic. Use the LLM only for: unstructured→structured
  RWA risk signals, written rationale, novel-event judgment, conversational UX.
  No AI-washing.
- **Mantle-only** (chain ID 5000). No other execution chains. Solana/Byreal is out.
- **Custody safety.** USDC is the only deposit asset. USDY & AUSD are sourced via
  **DEX, blocklist-aware**, never KYC-gated mint in the vault path. **No leverage/
  looping** (no RWA market on Mantle supports it). ALLOCATOR is a guardrail-bounded
  hot key with a kill switch.
- **Verify before integrating.** Treat addresses in `PLAN.md` as unverified until
  confirmed on-chain. Develop/test against `anvil --fork` of Mantle mainnet first;
  Phase-0 liquidity/oracle gates are mandatory.
- **Ground-truth reads via RPC** for held assets (Aave position, USDY NAV/DEX price,
  AUSD proof-of-reserves); 1delta is breadth/UX only.
- **Never commit secrets.** Git-ignored `.env` + documented `.env.example`. No
  secret logging.
- **Scope & execution discipline (MoSCoW + ROADMAP):** Must → Should → Could. Work
  in PR-sized tasks per `ROADMAP.md`; don't start a phase before the prior phase's
  exit criteria are met. Feature-freeze **2026-06-12**.

## Stack (do not substitute without asking)
Solidity + Foundry (forge/anvil/cast) · React + Vite + Tailwind + daisyUI · Node.js
+ TypeScript + Fastify · Vitest + Forge tests · Docker + Caddy/nginx · Z.AI · 1delta
API + Mantle RPC.

## Conventions
- TypeScript strict; no plain JS source. Solidity: explicit visibility, custom
  errors, NatSpec, checks-effects-interactions, reentrancy guards on fund-moving
  functions, prefer OpenZeppelin/Solmate.
- Comments explain non-obvious intent only; never narrate code or "explain the change."
- Every fund-moving contract needs Forge fork tests (happy path + guardrail
  violation + depeg/de-risk + liquidity-crunch withdrawal). Risk engine + validator
  need Vitest.

## Workflow
Branches `cursor/<descriptive-name>-46a8` (lowercase); one logical change per
commit; one PR per ROADMAP PR-group where practical; draft PRs via the PR tool. Keep
`PLAN.md` / `ROADMAP.md` / `AGENTS.md` / `CLAUDE.md` / this rule in sync. When unsure
about guardrails, custody, the 1delta boundary, or scope — **ask first.**
